1
00:02:25,969 --> 00:02:26,970
It’s not mine.

2
00:02:28,145 --> 00:02:29,210
It’s not yours?

3
00:02:29,973 --> 00:02:30,984
Seriously?

4
00:02:34,477 --> 00:02:35,507
I love you.

5
00:02:35,854 --> 00:02:36,820
Now…

6
00:02:37,021 --> 00:02:38,148
Are you still jealous?

7
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,265
Yeah?

8
00:02:43,737 --> 00:02:44,988
That’s what I thought.

9
00:02:45,321 --> 00:02:47,157
Surprise!

10
00:02:47,157 --> 00:02:49,033
Via, calm down, okay?

11
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:51,077
I’m sorry, I didn’t know
that was gonna happen.

12
00:02:51,077 --> 00:02:54,080
Once and for all, can you tell us
who this girl is in your life?

13
00:02:54,581 --> 00:02:57,625
That girl is more than
just a childhood friend,

14
00:02:58,168 --> 00:02:59,294
she’s my best friend.

15
00:03:00,086 --> 00:03:02,130
She’s the only girl I’ve ever loved.

16
00:03:03,882 --> 00:03:06,050
I’m flying back to Spain next week.

17
00:03:07,343 --> 00:03:08,511
Take care over there.

18
00:03:10,054 --> 00:03:14,601
And I hope your heart
finally finds its proper place.

19
00:03:14,838 --> 00:03:17,841
Always remember,
no matter what happens…

20
00:03:17,873 --> 00:03:20,418
I will always be your number one fan.

21
00:04:44,148 --> 00:04:48,236
Via, just always remember that
you may often be misunderstood.

22
00:04:48,236 --> 00:04:52,323
But what matters most is how
the people who truly know you see you.

23
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:57,591
I love you, my Via!
- Pretty Luna

24
00:05:02,208 --> 00:05:05,503
We’ll always be with you, okay?
You can’t be alone.

25
00:05:10,463 --> 00:05:13,258
Take care over there, and don’t be stupid!
- Y

26
00:05:16,306 --> 00:05:18,892
You’re still my baby, Via.

27
00:05:24,795 --> 00:05:27,379
Take care of your body
and your mental health. -Ke

28
00:05:29,606 --> 00:05:31,441
Well, you’re our friend now.
You don’t have a choice.

29
00:05:31,466 --> 00:05:32,548
She’s right!

30
00:05:41,205 --> 00:05:42,999
I’m sure you’ll come back home.

31
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:45,806
Take care, Via.Stay strong.
- The most handsome

32
00:05:46,878 --> 00:05:48,755
Go, Via! That’s my friend!

33
00:05:48,755 --> 00:05:49,881
– That’s my friend!
– What? You’re friends with Via?

34
00:05:49,881 --> 00:05:51,382
You’re not her friend.

35
00:05:58,060 --> 00:06:01,731
I promise, I’ll never let go.

36
00:06:07,774 --> 00:06:09,400
I love you…

37
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:55,321
You are my music.

38
00:07:15,383 --> 00:07:16,968
I promise, I’ll never let go.

39
00:07:17,413 --> 00:07:21,586
More handsome than the most
handsome! Sucks to be you, Sevi!

40
00:07:51,419 --> 00:07:53,171
Happy anniversary, love.

41
00:08:25,418 --> 00:08:27,546
Happy anniversary, my love.

42
00:08:28,164 --> 00:08:31,959
I hope this isn’t the last time
I’ll be saying or writing this.

43
00:08:32,376 --> 00:08:34,587
I know things have been hard for you.

44
00:08:34,959 --> 00:08:37,545
You’re probably having a tough
time juggling everything.

45
00:08:42,013 --> 00:08:44,849
It’s also getting harder to keep
our relationship a secret.

46
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:50,501
I know it’s hard, but please
let’s hang in there,

47
00:08:51,238 --> 00:08:52,907
I don’t want to lose you.

48
00:08:55,016 --> 00:08:59,876
We may have some misunderstandings,
actually a lot, of them.

49
00:08:59,901 --> 00:09:02,696
But know that those will never
make me love you any less.

50
00:09:03,857 --> 00:09:05,776
I’ll stay with you no matter what,

51
00:09:05,801 --> 00:09:07,219
as your girlfriend,

52
00:09:07,244 --> 00:09:08,662
best friend,

53
00:09:08,827 --> 00:09:10,454
and number one fan.

54
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:14,961
I love you.
Let’s stay strong together.

55
00:09:47,368 --> 00:09:49,829
City Council of Barcelona

56
00:10:05,595 --> 00:10:06,888
Market of the Conception

57
00:10:50,613 --> 00:10:52,490
Mira, how are you all there?

58
00:10:52,975 --> 00:10:54,435
We’re all right, Via.
Are you doing all right there?

59
00:10:54,435 --> 00:10:56,145
Are you eating properly?

60
00:10:58,522 --> 00:10:59,273
[In Spanish] Yes.

61
00:10:59,273 --> 00:11:03,361
I mean, yeah, of course.
I’m doing fine here.

62
00:11:03,361 --> 00:11:04,820
How’s Papa and everyone?

63
00:11:04,820 --> 00:11:06,197
We’re all really doing well.

64
00:11:06,197 --> 00:11:08,157
We miss you so much!

65
00:11:08,157 --> 00:11:09,533
We miss you, Via!

66
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:14,497
Hi sweetheart, don’t overwork yourself,
okay? Enjoy while you’re still young.

67
00:11:15,081 --> 00:11:16,311
Yes, Papa.

68
00:11:16,624 --> 00:11:17,291
Bye!

69
00:11:17,291 --> 00:11:18,251
- Love you, sweetheart.
- Via,

70
00:11:18,251 --> 00:11:19,001
Come home soon.

71
00:11:19,026 --> 00:11:20,420
Don’t forget my Spanish bread.

72
00:11:21,191 --> 00:11:22,692
I love you, sweetheart.

73
00:11:53,577 --> 00:11:54,592
Arkin?

74
00:11:56,624 --> 00:11:57,662
Via.

75
00:11:57,996 --> 00:11:59,498
What are you doing here?

76
00:12:02,378 --> 00:12:03,963
I will live here in Spain.

77
00:12:16,209 --> 00:12:17,810
[In Spanish] How are you?

78
00:12:17,935 --> 00:12:19,353
Very well.

79
00:12:19,353 --> 00:12:20,604
Good afternoon.

80
00:12:20,604 --> 00:12:21,897
Good evening.

81
00:12:21,897 --> 00:12:23,399
Merry Christmas.

82
00:12:23,941 --> 00:12:26,569
Let’s go! Everybody, let’s go.

83
00:12:26,569 --> 00:12:29,363
What are you saying?
Why are you here, huh?

84
00:12:29,363 --> 00:12:30,656
First of all,

85
00:12:30,656 --> 00:12:31,834
[In Spanish] do you speak Spanish?

86
00:12:32,241 --> 00:12:32,700
No.

87
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:36,679
You don’t know what you’re doing!
Get in the taxi and go home right now.

88
00:12:36,704 --> 00:12:38,581
It’s better if you don’t stay here.

89
00:12:39,290 --> 00:12:39,915
Okay?

90
00:12:39,915 --> 00:12:42,335
See? You don’t even know
how to speak Spanish, right?

91
00:12:42,335 --> 00:12:45,129
Now you’re here,
showing up out of nowhere.

92
00:12:45,129 --> 00:12:47,381
And why didn’t you even
say anything beforehand?

93
00:12:47,631 --> 00:12:49,633
You just suddenly show
up here, surprising people.

94
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:51,844
What about your school?
You have classes, right?

95
00:12:52,678 --> 00:12:54,764
Okay, before you get mad—

96
00:12:54,764 --> 00:12:56,349
- Huh?
- I do have school.

97
00:12:56,349 --> 00:12:58,117
- Okay.
- But we’re on a semester break right now.

98
00:12:58,142 --> 00:13:01,312
I’ll stay here for a month, and then
I’ll go home to finish my semester.

99
00:13:01,937 --> 00:13:03,189
So just relax.

100
00:13:04,732 --> 00:13:06,567
Why didn’t you say that earlier?

101
00:13:07,318 --> 00:13:10,112
Well, once I graduate,
I’m going to live here.

102
00:13:10,464 --> 00:13:11,798
I’m just fixing my paperwork.

103
00:13:18,245 --> 00:13:19,914
And why are you going to live here?

104
00:13:21,308 --> 00:13:23,268
Because you live here?

105
00:13:27,421 --> 00:13:29,215
What about your job?

106
00:13:29,899 --> 00:13:31,442
I’ll work here.

107
00:13:31,467 --> 00:13:35,610
I know some directors here.
I’ll work for them for experience,

108
00:13:35,635 --> 00:13:37,178
and then slowly build
my career from there.

109
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:39,517
So, don’t worry.

110
00:13:41,703 --> 00:13:43,100
I know what I’m doing.

111
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,356
Huh?

112
00:13:45,356 --> 00:13:46,565
It doesn’t really seem like it.

113
00:13:47,483 --> 00:13:51,529
It’s like you just woke up one day,
suddenly missed me so much,

114
00:13:51,529 --> 00:13:53,280
and booked a flight to come here.

115
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:56,033
Wow, how did you know?
That’s impressive.

116
00:13:56,582 --> 00:13:58,209
You’re here for a month, right?

117
00:13:58,744 --> 00:14:00,204
Does that mean you’re
spending Christmas here?

118
00:14:01,247 --> 00:14:03,541
Yes, right here. Is that okay?

119
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:05,418
Where are you going to stay?

120
00:14:07,002 --> 00:14:08,170
Right here.

121
00:14:10,706 --> 00:14:12,249
Do you have an
extra room here, Via?

122
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:14,300
I didn’t book a hotel.

123
00:14:17,096 --> 00:14:17,988
Wait a minute.

124
00:14:18,013 --> 00:14:20,766
Did Papa tell you where I live?

125
00:14:20,766 --> 00:14:21,655
Ouch—

126
00:14:22,393 --> 00:14:23,452
Yes.

127
00:14:23,477 --> 00:14:24,770
We asked your Aunt.

128
00:14:25,396 --> 00:14:26,967
It was supposed to be a surprise.

129
00:14:27,232 --> 00:14:29,276
If I asked you, then it wouldn’t
be a surprise anymore.

130
00:14:32,945 --> 00:14:34,738
Go to sleep now, get some rest.

131
00:14:35,281 --> 00:14:36,639
We have an early day tomorrow.

132
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:39,827
I’ll show you around Barcelona.

133
00:14:41,569 --> 00:14:42,746
I knew it.

134
00:14:42,746 --> 00:14:45,040
You want me here, too, right?

135
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,292
Right? Am I right?

136
00:14:46,292 --> 00:14:48,752
Get some rest now, sleep.

137
00:14:48,752 --> 00:14:50,254
- Okay.
- The bedroom is over there.

138
00:14:50,254 --> 00:14:51,230
There?

139
00:14:51,255 --> 00:14:52,069
Okay.

140
00:14:52,506 --> 00:14:55,301
Isn’t it like…
It’s just, I’m a visitor, so—

141
00:14:55,843 --> 00:14:57,069
- Straight, then—
- Okay.

142
00:14:57,391 --> 00:14:59,350
Straight, then left.

143
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:35,674
Wow!

144
00:17:37,087 --> 00:17:37,755
It’s beautiful!

145
00:17:37,755 --> 00:17:40,559
It’s even more beautiful in person.
Look, I’m getting goosebumps.

146
00:17:42,509 --> 00:17:44,261
That’s a masterpiece by Gaudí.

147
00:17:45,512 --> 00:17:47,754
You know, I’m actually thankful to him.

148
00:17:48,051 --> 00:17:51,596
For giving the world
something this beautiful.

149
00:17:55,105 --> 00:17:56,565
You know, I’m thankful, too.

150
00:17:56,982 --> 00:17:57,900
But not to Gaudí.

151
00:17:58,734 --> 00:18:00,693
Huh? To whom?

152
00:18:01,487 --> 00:18:02,571
To your parents.

153
00:18:02,922 --> 00:18:06,634
For giving the world
something this beautiful.

154
00:18:09,662 --> 00:18:11,455
Oh my gosh, whatever!

155
00:18:11,455 --> 00:18:12,529
But it’s true.

156
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,701
Gaudí can’t even compare.

157
00:18:19,781 --> 00:18:20,857
See?

158
00:18:21,465 --> 00:18:22,549
Thank you, lord.

159
00:18:22,901 --> 00:18:26,279
- That one! That one’s beautiful.
- That one?

160
00:18:26,553 --> 00:18:27,805
Well, I’m grateful to Auntie.

161
00:19:44,381 --> 00:19:45,758
It’s so nice here, Via.

162
00:19:46,950 --> 00:19:48,743
I don’t have to cover my face.

163
00:19:49,845 --> 00:19:51,472
No one recognizes me.

164
00:19:51,472 --> 00:19:52,639
There won’t be any issues.

165
00:19:55,267 --> 00:19:56,560
It’s just you and me.

166
00:19:57,436 --> 00:19:58,465
Free.

167
00:20:25,964 --> 00:20:27,674
It’s cold!

168
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:29,676
It’s cold!

169
00:20:36,975 --> 00:20:38,602
[In Spanish] Thank you.

170
00:20:42,397 --> 00:20:44,358
Thank you for showing me around here.

171
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:45,776
I know you’re busy.

172
00:20:46,777 --> 00:20:49,780
No problem. We still have a lot
of places to go tomorrow.

173
00:20:51,281 --> 00:20:53,742
Perfect. I still have a month here.

174
00:20:56,328 --> 00:20:57,788
Honestly, Larkin…

175
00:20:58,247 --> 00:20:59,873
Why did you really come here?

176
00:21:05,337 --> 00:21:06,713
For the whole month,

177
00:21:07,798 --> 00:21:09,508
I’ll convince you to work for me.

178
00:21:12,302 --> 00:21:14,304
Next month, I have a concert in Manila.

179
00:21:16,265 --> 00:21:19,476
That’s going to be my last concert,
so I’d like you to come.

180
00:21:20,394 --> 00:21:21,937
Last concert?

181
00:21:23,647 --> 00:21:25,232
I’m going to focus on being a director.

182
00:21:25,524 --> 00:21:28,527
Well, it’s not like my
very last concert ever.

183
00:21:29,695 --> 00:21:33,323
I still want to sing, but maybe
the next one will be far off.

184
00:21:34,116 --> 00:21:38,912
And I won’t take acting projects anymore,
series, movies, stuff like that.

185
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:43,267
Let me tell you now.

186
00:21:43,292 --> 00:21:45,043
You won’t be able to convince me
to go back to the Philippines.

187
00:21:45,043 --> 00:21:46,712
I just got back here.

188
00:21:47,212 --> 00:21:48,313
Hold on.

189
00:21:48,595 --> 00:21:51,306
Don’t shut me off so quickly,
I still have a month, remember?

190
00:21:51,911 --> 00:21:53,072
I haven’t even asked you yet.

191
00:21:53,097 --> 00:21:54,254
Okay, I’ll ask you now.

192
00:21:54,553 --> 00:21:55,762
Will you work for me, Via?

193
00:21:56,013 --> 00:21:56,864
No.

194
00:21:56,889 --> 00:21:57,903
Okay.

195
00:21:57,928 --> 00:21:58,801
Next time, then.

196
00:22:03,926 --> 00:22:04,972
Want some steak?

197
00:22:06,315 --> 00:22:07,465
Here.

198
00:22:12,195 --> 00:22:13,530
- Want some?
- Yeah.

199
00:22:49,536 --> 00:22:53,320
Hey, I really didn’t know that
he was your ex. How embarrassing.

200
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:55,322
I was fangirling a lot.

201
00:22:55,322 --> 00:22:57,950
I told you, Pauline.

202
00:22:57,950 --> 00:22:59,952
I told you he has a girlfriend.

203
00:23:00,243 --> 00:23:01,247
Oops—

204
00:23:01,411 --> 00:23:02,955
- Did you two get back together?
- Hey.

205
00:23:03,580 --> 00:23:04,706
Seriously, you two.

206
00:23:04,706 --> 00:23:06,416
Via might be uncomfortable—

207
00:23:06,416 --> 00:23:07,834
talking about this.

208
00:23:08,339 --> 00:23:11,009
I hope I get to see him
up close again.

209
00:23:11,088 --> 00:23:13,757
I’m sorry. He’s just really handsome.

210
00:23:13,882 --> 00:23:16,551
Do you know when he’ll
have a concert here again?

211
00:23:16,767 --> 00:23:18,769
I really want to watch him again.

212
00:23:19,388 --> 00:23:21,181
Right? You guys should come, too.

213
00:23:21,181 --> 00:23:22,481
I’ll think about it.

214
00:23:22,506 --> 00:23:23,379
Via!

215
00:23:26,603 --> 00:23:27,646
- Kino.
- Hi.

216
00:23:30,107 --> 00:23:32,943
Guys, this is Larkin.

217
00:23:32,943 --> 00:23:34,069
Hi, hello.

218
00:23:34,069 --> 00:23:35,070
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

219
00:23:35,070 --> 00:23:36,363
- My friends.
- Hello!

220
00:23:37,072 --> 00:23:38,699
He’s so handsome, oh my gosh!

221
00:23:39,825 --> 00:23:40,634
Hi.

222
00:23:40,659 --> 00:23:41,243
- Oh.
- Via.

223
00:23:41,243 --> 00:23:42,119
Auntie.

224
00:23:42,119 --> 00:23:43,245
Hi.

225
00:23:43,745 --> 00:23:47,082
No wonder you’ve been going home early.
You used to always work overtime.

226
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:52,421
Auntie, this is Larkin.

227
00:23:52,421 --> 00:23:53,005
- Kino,
- Hello.

228
00:23:53,005 --> 00:23:54,256
- This is my Aunt.
- Hi.

229
00:23:54,256 --> 00:23:57,300
So, you’re the one who asked
for my niece’s address, right?

230
00:23:57,884 --> 00:23:59,302
Yes. Thank you.

231
00:23:59,302 --> 00:24:01,680
Because of you, I was able to see her.

232
00:24:04,850 --> 00:24:07,602
Larkin, can I take a picture with you?

233
00:24:07,936 --> 00:24:09,271
- Take a picture of us.
- Just let her do it.

234
00:24:09,271 --> 00:24:09,813
Is it okay?

235
00:24:09,813 --> 00:24:10,313
Yes, sure.

236
00:24:10,313 --> 00:24:10,939
All right, stand here

237
00:24:10,939 --> 00:24:12,774
- Fine then.
- Come on, just help her out.

238
00:24:12,774 --> 00:24:14,443
Hold on. Make sure it’s good, okay?

239
00:24:14,443 --> 00:24:15,193
- I’m going to post it.
- Okay, okay.

240
00:24:15,193 --> 00:24:15,652
Via—

241
00:24:15,652 --> 00:24:16,695
Just one photo.

242
00:24:16,945 --> 00:24:18,488
- Via, if you ever want to—
- Okay.

243
00:24:19,309 --> 00:24:21,634
leave your job and go
back to the Philippines,

244
00:24:22,132 --> 00:24:23,515
just let me know, okay?

245
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:25,120
I know a lot of people there.

246
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:27,039
I can recommend you to them.

247
00:24:27,729 --> 00:24:28,932
All right, is that good?

248
00:24:28,957 --> 00:24:31,251
You don’t need to work for me anymore.

249
00:24:31,251 --> 00:24:31,877
Have some food.

250
00:24:31,877 --> 00:24:34,629
Auntie, I’m all right here.
I’ll stay here.

251
00:24:34,629 --> 00:24:36,798
- Are you sure?
- Yes, thank you very much.

252
00:24:37,007 --> 00:24:40,343
All right. But just let me know, okay?

253
00:24:40,677 --> 00:24:41,511
Yes.

254
00:24:41,511 --> 00:24:42,804
I’ll go ahead now,

255
00:24:42,804 --> 00:24:45,516
- I’m seeing my friends.
- All right.

256
00:24:46,808 --> 00:24:48,977
- Take care, Auntie.
- I watched your concert last time.

257
00:24:48,977 --> 00:24:50,395
Okay, I’ll go ahead now.

258
00:24:51,521 --> 00:24:52,689
Via, sit here.

259
00:24:52,689 --> 00:24:53,938
Okay.

260
00:24:53,982 --> 00:24:56,610
That was embarrassing,
so embarrassing.

261
00:24:56,610 --> 00:24:58,028
- Oh my gosh.
- Hey, you got your picture.

262
00:24:58,028 --> 00:25:00,072
You got your picture.

263
00:25:00,072 --> 00:25:01,073
Have you eaten yet?

264
00:25:01,930 --> 00:25:02,931
Not yet.

265
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,657
What do you want?

266
00:25:05,035 --> 00:25:06,286
- Pizza?
- Come on, let’s eat.

267
00:25:06,286 --> 00:25:07,996
How lucky.

268
00:25:07,996 --> 00:25:10,582
They’re being really sweet
right in front of us.

269
00:25:12,879 --> 00:25:13,774
So lucky.

270
00:25:15,087 --> 00:25:15,921
Just eat already.

271
00:25:15,921 --> 00:25:17,756
- Just let her be.
- Just eat.

272
00:25:50,585 --> 00:25:51,627
Hello.

273
00:25:51,698 --> 00:25:53,659
I’m almost done with class, Kino.

274
00:25:54,251 --> 00:25:55,752
Okay, I’ll meet up with you.

275
00:26:07,255 --> 00:26:08,298
Hey, Via!

276
00:26:08,431 --> 00:26:11,017
I went to every place you
told me about. All of them!

277
00:26:12,083 --> 00:26:13,209
Wow.

278
00:26:14,186 --> 00:26:15,257
You know—

279
00:26:16,314 --> 00:26:20,026
It's actually really nice walking around
without worrying about anything, right?

280
00:26:24,614 --> 00:26:27,265
I feel bad and happy at the same time.

281
00:26:27,290 --> 00:26:29,007
I’m happy for him
because this is the first

282
00:26:29,032 --> 00:26:31,804
time I’ve seen him
this happy and this free.

283
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:35,886
But I also feel bad that
he can only experience this abroad.

284
00:26:41,173 --> 00:26:43,675
Is that why you want to live
in another country?

285
00:26:44,676 --> 00:26:46,624
Yes. I told you.

286
00:26:48,513 --> 00:26:50,265
I want to work behind the camera.

287
00:26:51,270 --> 00:26:55,232
I want my privacy back,
even if that’s kind of impossible.

288
00:26:57,282 --> 00:26:59,033
And why here?

289
00:26:59,733 --> 00:27:02,360
Because you’re here.

290
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:03,343
Right?

291
00:27:04,029 --> 00:27:05,197
By the way,

292
00:27:05,353 --> 00:27:07,813
I met someone at the market,
the owner of the flower shop.

293
00:27:07,889 --> 00:27:09,557
She taught me some Spanish.

294
00:27:09,604 --> 00:27:10,429
Really?

295
00:27:11,286 --> 00:27:12,746
La florería.

296
00:27:14,432 --> 00:27:15,766
Flower shop.

297
00:27:15,999 --> 00:27:16,984
What else?

298
00:27:18,793 --> 00:27:20,086
Buenos días.
[Good morning.]

299
00:27:20,086 --> 00:27:21,129
Buenas tardes.
[Good afternoon.]

300
00:27:21,129 --> 00:27:22,589
Buenas noches.
[Good evening.]

301
00:27:24,533 --> 00:27:25,701
Anything else?

302
00:27:29,593 --> 00:27:31,598
Te ves muy guapa.
[You look very beautiful.]

303
00:27:35,734 --> 00:27:36,912
Oh, right—

304
00:27:45,228 --> 00:27:46,156
This is for you.

305
00:27:51,593 --> 00:27:53,136
Thank you.

306
00:27:53,270 --> 00:27:54,355
But why?

307
00:27:54,579 --> 00:27:55,956
Why flowers?

308
00:27:56,445 --> 00:27:57,707
Just because.

309
00:27:58,625 --> 00:28:01,294
Do I need a special occasion
to give you flowers?

310
00:28:02,170 --> 00:28:04,714
They’re called
“just-because flowers.”

311
00:28:05,257 --> 00:28:07,342
I have no reason to give them.

312
00:28:07,801 --> 00:28:09,261
I just want to.

313
00:28:09,261 --> 00:28:10,762
Just because.

314
00:28:15,219 --> 00:28:16,512
Thank you.

315
00:28:30,365 --> 00:28:31,366
Via.

316
00:28:33,243 --> 00:28:34,266
Yes?

317
00:28:37,247 --> 00:28:38,415
How are you holding up?

318
00:28:42,968 --> 00:28:45,095
I’m doing very well, Kino.

319
00:28:46,172 --> 00:28:49,050
I feel like I’m close
to achieving what I want.

320
00:28:50,617 --> 00:28:52,199
What do you want?

321
00:29:00,937 --> 00:29:01,813
Well,

322
00:29:03,690 --> 00:29:05,608
I’m afraid of people.

323
00:29:07,402 --> 00:29:08,820
Afraid of crowds.

324
00:29:11,031 --> 00:29:14,492
But I also really want to
go to your concert, Kino.

325
00:29:16,786 --> 00:29:20,457
But I’m afraid that I might just
end up back where I started.

326
00:29:24,002 --> 00:29:25,545
Maybe I won’t be able to handle it.

327
00:29:27,464 --> 00:29:28,923
But I’m trying.

328
00:29:30,425 --> 00:29:34,012
And I also know myself well enough
to know when I’ll be ready.

329
00:29:43,772 --> 00:29:45,815
I’m not gonna rush you, Via.

330
00:29:48,318 --> 00:29:50,904
You’ll be the one to
decide when you want to.

331
00:29:53,907 --> 00:29:55,492
Whatever decision you make,

332
00:29:56,326 --> 00:29:57,702
I’ll accept it.

333
00:29:59,037 --> 00:30:00,663
You can decide next month.

334
00:30:01,498 --> 00:30:02,415
Go get some rest.

335
00:30:06,169 --> 00:30:07,462
Good night, Kino.

336
00:30:08,797 --> 00:30:10,215
Good night, Via.

337
00:31:17,282 --> 00:31:20,827
I wanna write music, Kino.

338
00:32:31,981 --> 00:32:33,024
Cheers.

339
00:32:33,282 --> 00:32:34,616
Merry Christmas, Via.

340
00:32:34,859 --> 00:32:36,694
Merry Christmas, Kino.

341
00:32:40,132 --> 00:32:42,133
Wait a second,
I just need to get something.

342
00:32:42,158 --> 00:32:43,374
What is it?

343
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,300
Merry Christmas, Via.

344
00:33:01,466 --> 00:33:06,012
I just thought you’d want a new one.

345
00:33:06,804 --> 00:33:09,394
This is beautiful.

346
00:33:09,644 --> 00:33:12,772
Well, it’s time to let go of the past.

347
00:33:13,648 --> 00:33:15,358
So you can use this
for your future work.

348
00:33:19,779 --> 00:33:22,282
This is so beautiful.

349
00:33:25,577 --> 00:33:27,078
Thank you, Kino.

350
00:33:34,077 --> 00:33:35,120
My turn.

351
00:33:35,565 --> 00:33:37,108
I also have a gift for you

352
00:33:38,131 --> 00:33:39,173
What is it?

353
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:45,414
Tickets to your concert.

354
00:33:46,754 --> 00:33:47,880
Via?

355
00:33:49,115 --> 00:33:51,835
I will attend your concert, and...

356
00:33:53,563 --> 00:33:56,065
I want to write music for you, Kino.

357
00:33:58,735 --> 00:34:00,153
A-Are you sure?

358
00:34:00,603 --> 00:34:03,439
It hasn’t even been a month,
but I’m not complaining.

359
00:34:03,990 --> 00:34:04,975
Kino.

360
00:34:06,713 --> 00:34:08,077
I know when I’m ready.

361
00:34:09,579 --> 00:34:11,122
And I’m ready now.

362
00:34:18,091 --> 00:34:19,968
[INAUDIBLE]

363
00:34:25,062 --> 00:34:26,480
I love you, Via.

364
00:34:28,971 --> 00:34:33,351
In case you’re wondering,
I love you, too.

365
00:34:34,896 --> 00:34:37,398
I couldn’t catch it all.
What did you say?

366
00:34:39,350 --> 00:34:41,519
In case you’re wondering...

367
00:34:42,952 --> 00:34:44,871
I love you, too.

368
00:34:47,158 --> 00:34:48,409
You really love me?

369
00:34:48,961 --> 00:34:51,297
Yes. I love you very much.

370
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:54,524
This is the happiest Christmas for me.

371
00:34:58,726 --> 00:34:59,726
Kino!

372
00:35:04,221 --> 00:35:09,858
Merry Christmas.

373
00:35:29,812 --> 00:35:31,252
Are you available?

374
00:35:48,136 --> 00:35:49,124
Via!

375
00:35:50,179 --> 00:35:51,973
How are you? Feeling good?

376
00:35:53,099 --> 00:35:54,100
Yes, I’m okay.

377
00:35:55,101 --> 00:35:59,689
I’m just a little nervous,
especially when I hear the screams.

378
00:36:00,732 --> 00:36:01,858
You know, Via—

379
00:36:02,734 --> 00:36:04,610
I admire you as a person.

380
00:36:05,695 --> 00:36:07,046
You’re a brave woman

381
00:36:07,071 --> 00:36:12,368
I’m rooting for you, for your career,
and your relationship with Larkin.

382
00:36:12,577 --> 00:36:15,955
It may not be full of rainbows,
but it’s not full of storms either.

383
00:36:17,248 --> 00:36:18,916
You guys are made for each other.

384
00:36:18,916 --> 00:36:20,084
I witnessed that.

385
00:36:22,086 --> 00:36:23,504
Clea, thank you.

386
00:36:24,297 --> 00:36:27,091
I know you also did a lot for us.

387
00:36:27,091 --> 00:36:29,927
I want to tell you,
I want you to know...

388
00:36:30,762 --> 00:36:32,847
That we really appreciated it.

389
00:36:33,723 --> 00:36:36,017
I will always be cheering
for both of you.

390
00:36:41,981 --> 00:36:43,316
I’ll go ahead. Good luck!

391
00:36:43,691 --> 00:36:44,609
Thank you.

392
00:36:52,283 --> 00:36:53,534
Are you okay, love?

393
00:36:54,744 --> 00:36:55,787
Yes, love.

394
00:36:56,996 --> 00:36:58,122
We’re next.

395
00:36:58,539 --> 00:36:59,707
We can do this.

396
00:37:00,625 --> 00:37:03,586
Let’s sing the song
we wrote together.

397
00:37:04,837 --> 00:37:05,922
Let’s go?

398
00:37:11,469 --> 00:37:12,929
Wait, just curious…

399
00:37:13,930 --> 00:37:15,765
Are you okay with public proposals?

400
00:37:22,063 --> 00:37:24,398
Whatever it is, Arkin,

401
00:37:26,472 --> 00:37:28,194
I would still say yes.

402
00:37:36,734 --> 00:37:38,504
Ladies and gentlemen.

403
00:37:38,529 --> 00:37:41,491
Please welcome, Larkin Sanchez!

404
00:37:43,709 --> 00:37:46,170
Larkin Sanchez!

405
00:37:51,417 --> 00:37:55,045
♪ As I open my eyes,
you are with me ♪

406
00:37:55,085 --> 00:37:58,839
♪ We face the fight wherever we go ♪

407
00:37:58,908 --> 00:38:02,745
♪ We keep playing all
the way to school. ♪

408
00:38:02,770 --> 00:38:06,607
♪ Never apart, is this what
destiny has in store? ♪

409
00:38:07,227 --> 00:38:16,403
♪ Even if I grow fond of someone,
you are still the one I want to be with. ♪

410
00:38:17,493 --> 00:38:21,038
♪ No one else. ♪

411
00:38:21,038 --> 00:38:27,420
♪ With every look,
the tune I hear longs for you. ♪

412
00:38:28,428 --> 00:38:34,267
♪ For every minute,
I want to behold you. ♪

413
00:38:36,068 --> 00:38:42,658
♪ I don't know what this feeling is. ♪

414
00:38:43,735 --> 00:38:50,033
♪ Blending with the current
of my curious heart. ♪

415
00:38:51,235 --> 00:38:57,325
♪ You are my music's essence. ♪

416
00:38:57,325 --> 00:39:05,750
♪ Every voice on the guitar,
along with the storm of my mind. ♪

417
00:39:05,775 --> 00:39:16,452
♪ How can I say it when my
feelings deepen? Should I let it be? ♪

418
00:39:17,428 --> 00:39:23,184
♪ Or should I confess, what now? ♪

419
00:39:36,530 --> 00:39:39,992
♪ At the end of the day,
it's just you and me. ♪

420
00:39:39,992 --> 00:39:44,205
♪ The beauty of the clouds,
my feelings overflow. ♪

421
00:39:44,205 --> 00:39:47,708
♪ Sitting side by side with the guitar. ♪

422
00:39:47,708 --> 00:39:52,380
♪ Looking at you,
I feel my heart at ease. ♪

423
00:39:52,380 --> 00:39:56,175
♪ I feel the tremor in my heart— ♪

424
00:39:56,175 --> 00:40:05,309
♪ If not now, when will you
realize that I love you? ♪

425
00:40:05,309 --> 00:40:13,651
♪ What now?
I can't stay any longer. ♪

426
00:40:13,651 --> 00:40:20,950
♪ Don't tell me it's enough. ♪

427
00:40:20,950 --> 00:40:28,499
♪ I wish I had never met you. ♪

428
00:40:28,499 --> 00:40:36,632
♪ - Do you remember what you promised? ♪
♪ - Do you remember what you promised? ♪

429
00:40:36,632 --> 00:40:42,346
♪ You still are my music's essence. ♪

430
00:40:42,346 --> 00:40:46,642
♪ Every cry of the melody, ♪

431
00:40:47,393 --> 00:40:51,147
♪ In time with the beating of my heart. ♪

432
00:40:51,147 --> 00:41:02,450
♪ Forever holding your hand.
Staying by your side. ♪

433
00:41:02,475 --> 00:41:08,564
♪ - I promise, I will never let you go. ♪
♪ - I promise, I will never let you go. ♪

434
00:41:09,306 --> 00:41:17,356
♪ - I promise, I will never let you go. ♪
♪ - I will never let you go. ♪

435
00:41:17,381 --> 00:41:23,846
♪ - I promise, I will never let you go. ♪
♪ - I promise, I will never let you go. ♪

436
00:41:57,037 --> 00:41:58,497
I love you, Kino.

437
00:42:01,008 --> 00:42:02,593
I love you, Via.

438
00:42:25,825 --> 00:42:28,327
A round of applause
for my girlfriend,

439
00:42:28,327 --> 00:42:29,954
Avianna Rye Diaz!

440
00:42:32,748 --> 00:42:35,918
The love of my life.

441
00:42:38,796 --> 00:42:42,591
Finally, I can announce it
to the whole world.

442
00:43:15,833 --> 00:43:17,418
Kino? What are you doing?

443
00:43:18,002 --> 00:43:19,336
Is this what you were
asking about earlier?

444
00:43:19,336 --> 00:43:21,088
I told you before, no matter
what it is, my answer is yes.

445
00:43:21,088 --> 00:43:23,549
Stand up now, stand up.
Get up now, Kino!

446
00:43:26,594 --> 00:43:28,721
I’m just fixing something
with my pants.

447
00:43:32,349 --> 00:43:33,559
Scared you, huh?

448
00:43:38,147 --> 00:43:39,190
Relax.

449
00:43:46,553 --> 00:43:47,804
Are we done?

450
00:43:48,073 --> 00:43:49,658
We’re done singing, right?
So can we—

451
00:43:49,658 --> 00:43:50,826
Let’s go. Can we go back?

452
00:43:51,118 --> 00:43:52,828
- I’m going back.
- Is it over?

453
00:43:52,828 --> 00:43:54,079
I don’t think so.

454
00:47:05,553 --> 00:47:08,558
Red, orange, yellow.

455
00:47:09,733 --> 00:47:12,903
The colors of the sunset
always reminded me of her.

456
00:47:19,785 --> 00:47:23,247
The golden scenery that
witnessed how we started,

457
00:47:25,496 --> 00:47:26,598
ended,

458
00:47:27,038 --> 00:47:29,457
and started all over again.

459
00:47:31,188 --> 00:47:32,773
Running around,

460
00:47:32,798 --> 00:47:34,466
teasing each other,

461
00:47:34,466 --> 00:47:35,717
laughing.

462
00:47:39,187 --> 00:47:43,357
Slowly falling for each other,
confessing our feelings.

463
00:47:48,821 --> 00:47:51,615
Each moment,
colored by the sunset.

464
00:47:57,990 --> 00:47:59,011
Shining,

465
00:47:59,616 --> 00:48:00,743
happy.

466
00:48:04,587 --> 00:48:07,798
So I desperately tried to
hold on to these moments.

467
00:48:08,750 --> 00:48:10,627
In every song I wrote.

468
00:48:11,338 --> 00:48:13,132
In every movie I direct,

469
00:48:13,551 --> 00:48:15,503
I try to keep these moments.

470
00:48:20,661 --> 00:48:25,123
I was afraid that these moments
would disappear when tomorrow came.

471
00:48:29,480 --> 00:48:30,731
And I did.

472
00:48:30,731 --> 00:48:31,982
I lost her.

473
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:34,409
She was my whole world.

474
00:48:34,957 --> 00:48:37,085
I saw all the hardships
she went through.

475
00:48:38,238 --> 00:48:41,033
So I just wanted to make
each of her days better.

476
00:48:44,543 --> 00:48:45,961
But I couldn’t do it.

477
00:48:47,552 --> 00:48:50,596
Sometimes, because of things
I couldn’t control.

478
00:48:53,690 --> 00:48:58,039
But many times also
because of my mistakes,

479
00:48:59,050 --> 00:49:00,426
my shortcomings.

480
00:49:04,348 --> 00:49:06,464
Who am I without her?

481
00:49:07,726 --> 00:49:09,728
What color would my day
be when I’m alone?

482
00:49:11,581 --> 00:49:13,166
Would there still be
light in my tomorrow?

483
00:49:16,659 --> 00:49:20,079
Like Via, I had to face it.

484
00:49:21,432 --> 00:49:24,477
She had to break free
from the darkness of her past.

485
00:49:28,874 --> 00:49:33,879
And I had to accept that
not every tomorrow is bright.

486
00:49:35,305 --> 00:49:36,890
And that’s okay.

487
00:49:38,173 --> 00:49:40,573
A round of applause
for my girlfriend,

488
00:49:40,598 --> 00:49:42,267
Avianna Rye Diaz!

489
00:49:45,013 --> 00:49:48,058
The love of my life.

490
00:49:50,936 --> 00:49:54,773
Finally, I can announce
it to the whole world.

491
00:50:18,964 --> 00:50:20,972
Kino? What are you doing?

492
00:50:21,133 --> 00:50:22,467
Is this what you were
asking about earlier?

493
00:50:22,467 --> 00:50:24,094
I told you before, no matter
what it is, yes is my answer.

494
00:50:24,094 --> 00:50:26,888
Stand up now, stand up.
Get up now, Kino, please!

495
00:50:27,785 --> 00:50:32,081
I’ll just do it some other time…
I want it to be private between us.

496
00:50:35,289 --> 00:50:37,375
I’m just fixing something
with my pants.

497
00:51:02,381 --> 00:51:03,511
And cut!

498
00:51:03,675 --> 00:51:04,941
It’s a wrap, guys!

499
00:51:04,966 --> 00:51:05,894
Kiko.

500
00:51:06,345 --> 00:51:07,387
Very good, guys.

501
00:51:07,638 --> 00:51:08,597
Thank you very much.

502
00:51:08,597 --> 00:51:09,473
Thanks.

503
00:51:09,473 --> 00:51:10,597
I’m delighted.

504
00:51:11,090 --> 00:51:12,347
Thank you.

505
00:51:19,191 --> 00:51:20,734
Good job, love.

506
00:51:21,445 --> 00:51:22,780
Thank you, my love.

507
00:51:37,959 --> 00:51:39,961
What’s the movie about again?

508
00:51:40,462 --> 00:51:41,570
It’s about us.

509
00:51:42,339 --> 00:51:43,421
Huh?

510
00:51:44,174 --> 00:51:45,312
About us?

511
00:51:45,550 --> 00:51:49,012
Well, there’s a proposal
scene in it, right?

512
00:51:49,937 --> 00:51:51,897
You didn’t propose to me.

513
00:51:54,575 --> 00:51:57,202
Now, there is.

514
00:52:07,656 --> 00:52:08,657
Kino!

515
00:52:10,283 --> 00:52:11,660
Will you be my endgame?

516
00:52:26,883 --> 00:52:27,968
Yes.

517
00:52:30,721 --> 00:52:32,180
Yes, Kino.

518
00:52:32,848 --> 00:52:36,143
I told you, I’ll always answer yes.

519
00:53:29,667 --> 00:53:31,752
What’s the title of the film again?

520
00:53:34,993 --> 00:53:36,661
Golden Scenery Of Tomorrow.

521
00:55:06,460 --> 00:55:09,046
There’s still a whole
lifetime ahead of us, Via.

522
00:55:11,005 --> 00:55:12,715
And I’ll make sure.

523
00:55:14,141 --> 00:55:17,185
we spend every anniversary together.

524
00:55:17,483 --> 00:55:20,861
From the second, to the silver,

525
00:55:21,766 --> 00:55:24,311
even up to the centennial anniversary.

526
00:55:26,062 --> 00:55:28,544
You’re the only one
I want to grow old with.

527
00:55:36,531 --> 00:55:37,741
We’re getting married!

528
00:56:18,405 --> 00:56:20,491
The sunset may represent an end,

529
00:56:21,326 --> 00:56:24,037
but it always gave me hope
for a good tomorrow.

530
00:56:24,579 --> 00:56:26,331
A chance for a bright day.

531
00:56:26,933 --> 00:56:28,559
A chance to see her smile.

532
00:56:29,209 --> 00:56:31,461
A chance to be with each other again.

533
00:56:32,712 --> 00:56:34,748
A chance for forever with her.

534
00:56:57,927 --> 00:56:59,387
And, 3, 2, 1—

535
00:57:00,365 --> 00:57:01,407
Action!

536
00:57:01,722 --> 00:57:03,640
Action just started and you
already started laughing.

537
00:57:03,910 --> 00:57:06,246
- 3, 2, 1—
- Let’s be serious now.

538
00:57:06,246 --> 00:57:07,205
Action!

539
00:57:07,322 --> 00:57:08,532
I love you—

540
00:57:08,557 --> 00:57:10,844
- Oh, we’re starting again!
- Wait! Jo!

541
00:57:12,420 --> 00:57:14,631
- Cut for now.
- Wait a minute.

542
00:57:15,505 --> 00:57:16,715
- Here.
- Ouch!

543
00:57:17,131 --> 00:57:18,132
What was that? Was that real?

544
00:57:18,157 --> 00:57:19,617
That was real?

545
00:57:20,886 --> 00:57:22,012
I moved it.

546
00:57:22,524 --> 00:57:23,484
Ouch!

547
00:57:23,763 --> 00:57:24,614
Cut!

548
00:57:24,639 --> 00:57:25,640
Pinch him harder, Bea.

549
00:57:25,640 --> 00:57:27,100
Hey! That was already painful!

550
00:57:30,410 --> 00:57:31,344
Ouch!

551
00:57:33,815 --> 00:57:34,953
This is Samantha Vera. Samantha—

552
00:57:35,150 --> 00:57:36,401
- Oops.
- Here, see…

553
00:57:36,401 --> 00:57:37,527
I’m sorry, it didn’t stick.

554
00:57:37,527 --> 00:57:38,945
That was a slap!

555
00:57:38,945 --> 00:57:39,797
They’re at—

556
00:57:40,271 --> 00:57:41,230
- Why not A—
- Cut!

557
00:57:43,170 --> 00:57:46,048
Do you remember—

558
00:57:47,120 --> 00:57:50,165
Arkin! Why couldn’t—

559
00:57:50,165 --> 00:57:50,957
- I’m sorry.
- Rolling.

560
00:57:50,957 --> 00:57:52,042
Welcome to—

561
00:57:52,242 --> 00:57:53,452
- the Q and A—
- The—

562
00:57:53,983 --> 00:57:55,526
- Oh my god!
- I didn’t hear it.

563
00:57:55,551 --> 00:57:57,178
A round of applause—

564
00:57:57,203 --> 00:57:58,204
What was it again?

565
00:57:58,256 --> 00:58:00,050
- To my girlfriend?
- Yes.

566
00:58:00,050 --> 00:58:01,217
A round of—

567
00:58:01,468 --> 00:58:02,469
One more time…

568
00:58:02,469 --> 00:58:03,178
A round of applause—

569
00:58:03,178 --> 00:58:03,928
Sam, what—

570
00:58:03,928 --> 00:58:05,430
Oops, you’re Yanna.

571
00:58:11,694 --> 00:58:12,719
Real cut!

572
00:58:14,397 --> 00:58:15,940
You could be an actor—

573
00:58:17,108 --> 00:58:18,610
Are you still breathing?

574
00:58:20,697 --> 00:58:21,719
One more time.

575
00:58:24,198 --> 00:58:25,199
I’m sorry!

576
00:58:25,224 --> 00:58:26,350
It won’t go in.

577
00:58:29,370 --> 00:58:30,360
You can bite now.

578
00:58:32,373 --> 00:58:33,249
Again?

579
00:58:33,249 --> 00:58:35,001
- Over there, right?
- They just said it.

580
00:58:35,001 --> 00:58:36,461
- Huh?
- Sorry.

581
00:58:36,461 --> 00:58:37,921
Cut. Sorry.

582
00:58:37,921 --> 00:58:38,963
You’re a side-chick!

583
00:58:38,963 --> 00:58:40,048
You’re ugly!

584
00:58:40,048 --> 00:58:41,549
Ugly!

585
00:58:41,549 --> 00:58:45,011
I don’t want to pass
all my wounds and fears—

586
00:58:47,388 --> 00:58:50,225
I’m not… I didn’t fight anyone,
nothing to do with that.

587
00:58:51,559 --> 00:58:52,453
Fight?

588
00:58:53,186 --> 00:58:53,812
And—

589
00:58:53,812 --> 00:58:57,273
You don’t know what you’re doing! Get in—

590
00:58:58,858 --> 00:58:59,901
- “In case.”
- “In case.”

591
00:59:00,777 --> 00:59:02,403
In case—

592
00:59:02,403 --> 00:59:03,780
- What was it? One more…
- Cut!

593
00:59:04,447 --> 00:59:06,032
Hey, so flirtatious.

594
00:59:06,057 --> 00:59:07,308
Such a cheeky flirt.

595
00:59:10,120 --> 00:59:11,133
Cut!

596
00:59:13,832 --> 00:59:15,208
All right.

597
00:59:16,501 --> 00:59:17,297
Let’s switch.

598
00:59:18,711 --> 00:59:19,503
Okay, cut.

599
00:59:19,528 --> 00:59:20,863
- Cut!
- Let’s cut.
